<mods xmlns="http://www.loc.gov/mods/v3" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" ID="T_668" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.loc.gov/mods/v3     http://claudia:claudia@data.stonesutras.org:8080/exist/webdav/db/schema/mods-3-0.xsd"><titleInfo lang="zh"><title>佛說不增不減經</title></titleInfo><titleInfo transliteration="pinyin"><title>Fo shuo buzeng bumie jing</title></titleInfo><titleInfo lang="en" type="translated"><title>Sutra Spoken by the Buddha of Neither Increase Nor Decrease</title></titleInfo><titleInfo lang="sa"><title>*Anūnatvâpūrṇatva-nirdeśa-parivarta</title></titleInfo><titleInfo type="reference"><title>T#668, 16</title></titleInfo><name xmlns:ns2="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" ns2:href="#putiliuzhi" type="personal"><namePart lang="zh"/><namePart transliteration="pinyin"/><namePart lang="sa">Bodhiruci</namePart><role><roleTerm>compiler</roleTerm></role></name><physicalDescription><extent><detail type="fascicle">1</detail></extent></physicalDescription><abstract>The Buzeng bujian jing, translated by Bodhiruci in 525 (Skt. *Anūnatvâpūrṇatva-nirdeśa-parivarta); 1 fasc.; T 668. A short but influential
        tathāgatagarbha text that discusses the relationship between sentient beings and the dharmakāya 法身 (or dharmadhātu 法界) as being one of equivalence
        within the medium of the tathāgatagarbha 如來藏. The sermon begins with a question by Śāriputra 舎利弗 as to whether the total number of sentient beings
        who transmigrate through the three realms and six destinies ever increases or decreases. The Buddha responds by explaining how views of increase and decrease
        are equivalent to the mistaken extremes of eternalism and nihilism. He then goes into depth explaining the nature of the tathāgatagarbha in relation to the
        dharma body and sentient beings. [Charles Muller; source(s): Hirakawa, JEBD]</abstract><originInfo><dateOther>525</dateOther></originInfo><relatedItem xmlns:ns2="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" ns2:href="Taisho" type="host"><titleInfo lang="ja"><title>大正新脩大藏經.</title></titleInfo><titleInfo transliteration="romaji"><title>Taishō shinshū daizōkyō</title></titleInfo><titleInfo transliteration="romaji" type="abbreviated"><title>Taishō</title></titleInfo><titleInfo lang="en" type="translated"><title>New edition of the Buddhist canon in the Taishō era</title></titleInfo><name ns2:href="#takakusu" type="personal"><namePart lang="ja" type="family">高楠</namePart><namePart lang="ja" type="given">順次郎</namePart><role><roleTerm>editor</roleTerm></role></name><name ns2:href="#watanabe" type="personal"><namePart lang="ja" type="family">渡邊</namePart><namePart lang="ja" type="given">海旭</namePart><role><roleTerm>editor</roleTerm></role></name><physicalDescription><extent><detail type="volume">85</detail></extent></physicalDescription><originInfo><dateIssued>1924-1932</dateIssued><dateIssued encoding="marc" point="start">1924</dateIssued><dateIssued encoding="marc" point="end">1932</dateIssued><place><placeTerm>Tōkyō</placeTerm></place><publisher><name type="corporate"><namePart lang="ja">大正一切經刊行會</namePart><namePart transliteration="pinyin">Taishō issaikyō kankōkai</namePart></name></publisher></originInfo><part><detail type="volume"><number>16</number></detail><extent unit="page"><start>466a</start><end>468a</end></extent></part></relatedItem></mods>